HEADWORD: Pandiculation
<hw>Pan*dic`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pandiculari</ets> to stretch one's self, fr. <ets>pandere</ets> to
spread out.]</ety> <def>A stretching and stiffening of the trunk and
extremities, as when fatigued and drowsy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pandit</ent>⟦br⟧
